latestIgtvVideos.title: PRADA RE- EDITION 2000
latestIgtvVideos.caption: I’ve never really been a big fan of Prada’s designs. I’ve always felt their designs were too manly and structured. But this mini bag I had to bring home. I’ve been thinking of purchasing this one for a while but since SF does not have a Prada boutique ( I know !! 🙄) and ya girl loves to get her designer bags from the boutiques only! I have a lot of reasons why but anyways so I had to drive to San Jose to track this little baby. Urghh I know things we do for things. 🙄 But in the end it was all worth it. I love love love this bag small yet fits everything I need, easy to style and easy on your bank 🤣🤣 - Thank you for watching ❤️ #pradareedition2000

latestIgtvVideos.title: Live, Laugh and Lavender 💜
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
⁣⁣⁣ My Lavender dream come true: I have always wanted to visit a Lavender field and thought I would have to travel all the way to Europe to realize the dream but little did I know that this beautiful Lavender farm was just 45 mins drive from my home! We set up a little picnic under a tree while enjoying some fresh cut fruits cheese and a glass of wine. We went in the evening so the breeze was coming in filling the entire air with the sweet smell of Lavender. It was almost golden hour when I decided to run along the field to capture this moment and this is exactly how I was feeling within as well - HAPPY!! ⁣
⁣📹 @tenyang01 ⁣⁣

Thank you for carrying the weight of a wounded nation on your back with grace, laughter, and boundless compassion. Where many would have broken, you forgave. Where others sought revenge, you offered wisdom.

You taught us that freedom begins in the mind, that joy is not the absence of suffering, but the presence of love. In every corner of the world, from the highest halls to the quietest hearts, you have sown seeds of kindness, truth, and unity. 

May you live long. May your heart remain light.
May your legacy echo into the eternity.

With boundless devotion and love,
༄༅།། The children of Tibet and all who walk your path

Happiest 90th Birthday Ghongsachok 🙏🏼

Thank you @tibet_effect for this soul altering music and voice and @tenziitsewang for compiling such a beautiful documentary of the Dalai Lama. One can clearly see it’s not just talent but a true labor of love.  Thank you both for allowing me to use your gift to our precious Kundun enabling me to express mine. I am eternally grateful to artists like you and many who not just bring their talent but their whole f heart to the art and turn it into magic. Art and artists hold a sacred space in society—beyond decoration or entertainment, they are truth-tellers, healers, and timekeepers of the human experience. 
In times of despair, art becomes refuge.
In times of joy, celebration.
In revolution, it becomes protest.

Artists don’t just create—they feel, they translate, and they transform.

Special little shout out to the beautiful kids of TCV singing their hearts out. No doubt their voice shifted the whole energy and experience of the already super emotionally powerful song. Thank you

Part 2️⃣👀 Bylakupee dairies 

📍bikers restaurant tdl ( best momo and sha baklep) they are only open during the day time. They make some wicket virgin mojitos too 
📍Hogo (hotpot) zhakang sera rd. Literally everything on the menu is bomb. My fav is jhinstel sha and tingmo (yummmm) 
📍Red Table 1st camp( that’s what we call it cus they have RED TABLES 🤣) their breakfast is so famous there was no need to name the restaurant. A tiny little joint that serves fresh puri or baklep with Choley, aloo, eggs, so good!!! Their coffee is creamy and rich. Love it 
📍frozen yogurt place at Bhumtso complex 3rd camp had really delicious frozen yogurt. They also have a lot of toppings… I get my sugar rush fixed here !!!! So good !!! 
📍Druk Samphel 4th camp complex will take you straight to Thimphu 😭 their thali is to die for… the shakam and Erma dhtseee luxuriously creamy and soul filling. Must must try 
📍Tibet village resort go to place to find some peace and quiet with Bali feels.. their orders take some time to arrive but once it’s there you’ll forget it took its sweet time. Great food, ambience and service

COMING TO 📍BYLAKUPEE? HERE ARE MY RECOMMENDATIONS 🦋🦋🦋🦋

In no particular order!!!! Love these places to the core.. 
📍BUDDHA CAFE 1st camp (best coffee/pasteries/ service) 
📍KUNAM KITCHEN 3rd camp. Their veggie momo is my FAVORITE 🫶🏼 everything on the menu is bomb but.. veg momo khotey has my heart 🤓 
📍LAPHING at camp 4 next to the fruit seller is 🔥 I get it with everything, wai wai, peanuts and runny 🤧🤧 so good. 
📍GHANGRI TACHOK 1st camp has the best hand pulled noodles, kyurtsel (chive) momo 🤤😋 owned and run by very sweet Amdo family with five kids 🥹 show them some love and enjoy this wholesome hole in wall restaurant. 

Stay tuned for other recs CUS baby BYLAKUPEE is coming for you !!!!! So grateful 🙈😭🫶🏼.
